    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.14105v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        The symmetry SU(2) and its geometric Bloch Sphere rendering are familiar for a qubit (spin-1/2) but extension of symmetries and geometries have been investigated far less for multiple qubits, even just a pair of them, that are central to quantum information. In the last two decades, two different approaches with independent starting points and motivations have come together for this purpose. One w&hellip;
