      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.14086v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        We present a linearly arrayed, 16-element, superconducting nanowire single-photon detector with 83.4$\%$ system detection efficiency at 1550 nm and a mean per-element dead-time of 9.6-ns, enabling counting at 1 giga-count per second with $&gt;50\%$ System Detection Efficiency. This device was designed and fabricated in an existing scalable commercial process.
        
