        Fluoride crystals doped with rare-earth ions (REI) and pair centers in diamond for fast ($10^{-9}\rm{s}$) quantum computers (FQC) are proposed. As specific systems for REI doping, we propose $Ca_{1-x}Sr_{x}F_{2}$ crystals and their analogues. The $^{4}f$-states with different total orbital angular moments of these ions serve as two-level systems (qubits). Suitable REIs are proposed as well. It is&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.13319v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.13319v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
